><div><ul><ul><ul><li>Student (m/w/d) der Informatik, Elektrotechnik oder eines vergleichbaren Studiengangs</li>\n<li>Erfahrung in der Strukturierung von Daten sowie mit Datenstrukturen (SQL, JSON)</li>\n<li>Erfahrung mit Python und Grundkenntnisse in Pandas oder Spark w&uuml;nschenswert</li>\n<li>Gute Analysef&auml;higkeiten</li>\n<li>Strukturierte und eigenst&auml;ndige Arbeitsweise</li>\n</ul></ul></ul></div></div></div><div><div><h2 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><div><b>Gute Gr&uuml;nde, um bei HARTING durchzustarten:</b></div></h2>\n<p>Das Wichtigste zuerst: Bei uns z&auml;hlen Sie als Mensch &ndash; deshalb bieten wir Ihnen Benefits an, die Sie im Job und Privat unterst&uuml;tzen.</p>\n </div><div></div><div><div><div><div><div><div><b>Betreuung</b><b>:</b><br>\nIntensive Betreuung durch Experten* in Ihrem Bereich</div></div><br>\n</div></div>\n<div></div><b>Networking</b><b>:</b><br>\nSpezielle Networking-Events f&uuml;r unsere Studierenden</div>\n </div><div></div><div><div><div><div><b>Faire Verg&uuml;tung</b><b>:</b><br>\nFaire Verg&uuml;tung ab Tag 1</div></div><br>\n</div></div>\n<div></div><b>Flexibilit&auml;t</b><b>:</b><br>\nVielf&auml;ltige Gleitzeit- und Teilzeitmodelle, mobile Arbeit, flexible Mittagspause</div>\n</div></div><div><h2 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><div><b>Gute Gr&uuml;nde, um bei HARTING durchzustarten:</b></div></h2>\n<p>Das Wichtigste zuerst: Bei uns z&auml;hlen Sie als Mensch &ndash; deshalb bieten wir Ihnen Benefits an, die Sie im Job und Privat unterst&uuml;tzen.</p>\n<ul><li><b>Betreuung</b><b>:</b><br>\nIntensive Betreuung durch Experten* in Ihrem Bereich</li><li><b>\nNetworking</b><b>:</b><br>\nSpezielle Networking-Events f&uuml;r unsere Studierenden</li>\n<li><b>Faire Verg&uuml;tung</b><b>:</b><br>\nFaire Verg&uuml;tung ab Tag 1</li><li><b>\nFlexibilit&auml;t</b><b>:</b><br>\nVielf&auml;ltige Gleitzeit- und Teilzeitmodelle, mobile Arbeit, flexible Mittagspause</li></ul></div></div>"}
{"company_name": "SAP Aktiengesellschaft", "job_title": "Intern (f/m/d) (6 months): Data Engineering & Data Science in Business Operations", "job_description": "<div><p><b>Requisition ID: </b>280126<br>\n<b>Work Area: </b>Corporate Operations<br>\n<b>Location: </b>Berlin<br>\n<b>Expected Travel: </b>0 - 10%<br>\n<b>Career Status: </b>Student<br>\n<b>Employment Type: </b>Limited Full Time</p><p></p><p><b><br>\nCOMPANY DESCRIPTION</b></p><p>\nSAP started in 1972 as a team of five colleagues with a desire to do something new. Together, they changed enterprise software and reinvented how business was done. Today, as a market leader in enterprise application software, we remain true to our roots. That&rsquo;s why we engineer solutions to fuel innovation, foster equality and spread opportunity for our employees and customers across borders and cultures.</p><p>\nSAP values the entrepreneurial spirit, fostering creativity and building lasting relationships with our employees. We know that a diverse and inclusive workforce keeps us competitive and provides opportunities for all. We believe that together we can transform industries, grow economics, lift up societies and sustain our environment. Because it&rsquo;s the best-run businesses that make the world run better and improve people&rsquo;s lives.</p><p></p><p><b><br>\nABOUT THE TEAM</b><br>\nThe Technology &amp; Innovation (T&amp;I) board area manages SAP&acute;s overall platform, technology and innovation strategy.<br>\nT&amp;I drives the incubation of new ventures (SAP.iO), the development of innovative solutions, and the engineering of intelligent technologies (ML, AI, IoT, etc.) to build a fully integrated, extensible foundation for all SAP applications &ndash; the SAP Business Technology Platform (SAP BTP).</p><p>\nThe New Ventures &amp; Technologies (NVT) unit within the T&amp;I board area has the mission to pursue transformative growth by exploring new markets and new-to-world solutions. Technology innovation and product incubation build the core business.</p><p>\nThe Berlin Operations and Business Insights team is part of the NVT unit and is responsible for operational, analytical, and project management tasks for SAP Labs Berlin and its Chief Operating Officer (COO). The team also functions as cross-departmental and cross-board support to enable internal and external collaboration-projects and establish business processes by turning creative thinking into innovative solutions pursuing an end-to-end responsibility approach for all projects in record time.</p><p>\nSAP Labs Berlin was established to be the frontrunner and thought leader in enterprise application software. We strengthen SAP's position as a pioneer and innovation driver in and around Berlin through strategic and customer-centric projects. We contribute to Europe's leading startup ecosystem and continuously engage with technology startups of the future. We strive for operational excellence and best run internal processes.</p><p></p><p><b><br>\nTHE ROLE</b><br>\nThe SAP Berlin Operations &amp; Business Insights team supports the COO of SAP Labs Berlin with day-to-day operations and the management and execution of high-profile strategic projects.<br>\nYou will be part of the analytics division, which thrives in deconstructing and re-creating business processes to meet changing strategic and operational needs. Thereby we enable colleagues to make data-driven decisions and drive operational excellence. You will support us by combining an analytical mindset and thought leadership to drive the digitization of our business operations.</p><p>\nDuring your internship you will design, implement and maintain data-driven processes. This involves requirements gathering to identify relevant data sources and integrating those sources into our data warehouse by setting up ETL pipelines. Finally, you will model the data and create meaningful visualizations to support critical business decisions. You might also explore Machine Learning use cases.</p><p>\nFurthermore, as part of the T&amp;I New Ventures &amp; Technologies organization, you will have the opportunity to participate in strategic projects and present your proposals and demonstrate their impact to key stakeholders within our organization.</p><p><br>\nYour core tasks include but are not limited to:</p><ul><li>\nDesigning and implementing data-driven decision-making processes</li><li>\nCommunicating effectively to identify stakeholders needs and translating them into appropriate requirements.</li><li>\nBuilding ETL pipelines to integrate data from various sources.</li><li>\nModelling and analyzing data to extract important business insights and give recommendations to strategic stakeholders.</li><li>\nWorking with business analysts and project consultants on strategic projects to improve business processes within our team.</li><li>\nOptional: Exploring machine learning use cases</li></ul><p></p><p><b><br>\nROLE REQUIREMENTS</b></p><ul><li>\nStudent (f/m/d) at a university or a university of applied sciences</li><li>\nPreferred fields of study: Data Science, Business Informatics, Statistics, Computer Science, Business Analytics, Economics, Operations Research or similar</li><li>\nExperience with decomposing and solving real world business problems with analytical rigor</li><li>\nAbility to learn new tools rapidly and independently</li><li>\nProficiency in Python or R</li><li>\nPractical experience in ETL development</li><li>\nKnowledge in SQL, data structures, data modeling, or data warehousing</li><li>\nExperience with or willingness to learn Business intelligence tools like SAP Analytics Cloud, Tableau or Power BI</li><li>\nExperience in developing and deploying machine learning models is a plus.</li><li>\nLanguage skills: English proficiency required; German is a plus</li><li>\n6 months full-time availability is mandatory</li><li>\nStart date: as soon as possible / latest October 2021</li></ul><p></p><p><i><br>\nYour set of application documents should contain a cover letter, a resume in table form, school leaving certificates, certificate of enrollment, current university transcript of records, copies of any academic degrees already earned, and if available, references from former employers (including internships). Please also describe your experience and skills in foreign languages and computer programs / programming languages.</i><br>\n<i>Please also include possible start dates for your internship.</i></p><p><br>\n #Internship #Praktikum #Germany #Deutschland #Berlin #Student #Analytics #DataEngineering #DataScience #Businessintelligence #Bizops #Businessoperations</p><p></p><p><b><br>\nWHAT YOU GET FROM US\n</b></p><p>Success is what you make it. At SAP, we help you make it your own.</p><p>\nA career at SAP can open many doors for you. If you&rsquo;re searching for a company that&rsquo;s dedicated to your ideas and individual growth, recognizes you for your unique contributions, fills you with a strong sense of purpose, and provides a fun, flexible and inclusive work environment &ndash; apply now<i>.</i></p><p></p><p><b><br>\nSAP'S DIVERSITY COMMITMENT</b><br>\nTo harness the power of innovation, SAP invests in the development of its diverse employees. We aspire to leverage the qualities and appreciate the unique competencies that each person brings to the company.</p><p>\nSAP is committed to the principles of Equal Employment Opportunity and to providing reasonable accommodations to applicants with physical and/or mental disabilities. If you are in need of accommodation or special assistance to navigate our website or to complete your application, please send an e-mail with your request to Recruiting Operations Team (Americas: Careers.NorthAmerica@sap.com or Careers.LatinAmerica@sap.com, APJ: Careers.APJ@sap.com, EMEA: Careers@sap.com).</p><p>\nSuccessful candidates might be required to undergo a background verification with an external vendor.</p></div><p></p>"}
{"company_name": "Smart Steel Technologies GmbH", "job_title": "Machine Learning or Python Developer Working Student (m/f/d) - Industrial Data Science and Software", "job_description": "<div><p>APPLYING MACHINE LEARNING TO PROCESSES, NOT PEOPLE<br>\n</p><p></p><p>\nAt Smart Steel Technologies, we are building a one-of-a-kind cross-disciplinary team, uniting the worlds of steel and machine learning. Our team has come together from a diverse set of academic and professional backgrounds: software development, computer science, mathematics, physics, and metallurgy. Our goal is to leverage this expertise through trust and cooperation. We want to foster an environment where team members have frequent opportunities to learn from each other in fields that they are not (yet) experts.</p><br>\n<p></p><p>\nThe machine learning and data science we employ comes in several varieties: image processing, signal processing, classical supervised modeling, unsupervised methods, and fundamental statistics and probability. As a machine learning working student, your specific expertise as well as your motivation would be the major factors in determining your day-to-day work.</p><br>\n<p></p><p>\nWe are grateful to stand on the shoulders of the open source giants. We use NumPy-flavored Python3 as the basis for our development, taking advantage of the availability of libraries designed for both software engineering and data science, ranging from Flask to SciPy, SQLAlchemy to Keras, Jupyter to Pandas, and many more. When Python&rsquo;s time or space complexity becomes a constraint, we turn to modern C++. When we require client-side browser-based interactivity, we turn to JavaScript.</p><br>\n<p></p><p>\nABOUT THE JOB</p>\n<ul><li><p>\nApply modern machine learning methods to optimization and quality problems in industrial processes</p></li><li><p>\nTune and optimize neural networks, both bespoke and pre-architected; shallow, deep and recurrent</p></li><li><p>\nDevelop and provision software for online learning and prediction in industrial systems</p></li></ul><br>\n<p></p><p>\nQUALIFICATIONS THAT CATCH OUR EYE</p>\n<ul><li><p>\nBachelor&rsquo;s or Master&rsquo;s in Computer Science, Statistics, Mathematics, Physics or Engineering</p></li><li><p>\nExperience in working with raw and unstructured industrial data sets</p></li><li><p>\nExperience in software engineering or operations, especially in a full-stack development environment</p></li><li><p>\nExperience with modern web technologies</p></li><li><p>\nFluency in German and Russian is a plus; English is required</p></li></ul><br>\n<p></p><p>\nBENEFITS</p>\n<p>\n</p><ul><li>Transparency of business strategies</li><li>\nAutonomy balanced by responsibility</li><li>\nCohesive, multidisciplinary team</li><li>\nMeaningful industrial problems</li><li>\nModern machine learning techniques</li><li>\nSleek, new office located in Berlin</li><li>\nProfessional educational opportunities</li><li>\nGerman language courses and public transport included</li></ul></div>"}
{"company_name": "Sandgate Systems Ltd", "job_title": "Junior Data Analyst (full-time, w/m/x)", "job_description": "Junior Data Analyst\n<br><br>\nWe\u2019re offering a fantastic professional growth opportunity as a Junior Data Analyst. You are a data aficionado and love to crunch large amounts of numbers? Come join our fast-growing team and have an unique impact on the strategic development of our international startup through actionable data insights!\n<br><br>\nAufgaben\n<br><br>\n<ul>\n<li>Introduce and support the Setup of our BI function</li>\n<li>You have already been able to gain experience within the Data-Analyst landscape</li>\n<li>You use data to identify patterns and use them to make forecasts for the future</li>\n<li>Design, develop and optimize our data and reporting landscape incl. Visualization</li>\n<li>Monitor and improve our tracking set-up incl. DataLayer, GTM, GA</li>\n<li>Analyze and optimize performance of our main online marketing channels (Instagram, Facebook, Youtube, Google, CRM & Influencer Marketing) to derive actionable insights for the marketing team to improve our marketing performance (customer acquisition and retention)</li>\n<li>Work closely with CEOs to establish specific goals and strategies, define processes and frameworks</li>\n</ul>\nQualifikation\n<br><br>\n<ul>\n<li>You have gained working experience in the BI space</li>\n<li>You have a university degree, preferably with a strong quantitative background \u2013 e.g. Business, Data Science, Economics, Mathematics, Statistics, Finance, or a social science with a highly quantitative profile</li>\n<li>You have experience in all common web analytics tools and tag managers</li>\n<li>You have experience with the Facebook Business Manager</li>\n<li>You may have previously successfully set-up the data infrastructure and reporting of a scale-up (preferably with BigQuery)</li>\n<li>You have a strong business sense and possess strong and analytical and visual thinking skills, with the ability to identify business questions, pain points and opportunities</li>\n<li>You constantly are looking for ways to improve and optimize processes</li>\n<li>You have good communication skills and can clearly express and delegate tasks, strategies and general requirements</li>\n<li>You are a team player and are constantly trying to achieve success for the company as a whole</li>\n</ul>\nBenefits\n<br><br>\n<ul>\n<li>Gain ownership and shape an early-stage startup from the ground up</li>\n<li>Be part of an inspiring workplace built on trust, empowerment and feedback</li>\n<li>Substantial creative freedom to execute smart ideas</li>\n<li>Work in a high-energy office located in the heart of Berlin</li>\n<li>Be part of a fast-paced entrepreneurial culture with bold ambitions</li>\n<li>Access to mind-blowingly good and healthy food and drinks</li>\n<li>Team events and amazing get-togethers with our growing influencer and food expert community</li>\n</ul>\nAbout Every.\n<br><br>\nOperating in a unique setting with a distinct unfair advantage, we leverage +40 years of industry expertise and state of the art means of production and combine it with the agility of a start-up to reinvent convenience food: We\u2019re on a mission to make good\\* food accessible to everyone, everywhere and anytime.\n<br><br>\nTo us, good\\* food means tasty, healthy and ecologically and socially sustainable food.\n<br><br>\nIn co-creation with leading food experts, we create mind-blowing ready-meals to enable everyone to flexibly eat healthy even when in a hurry. All our meals are:\n<br><br>\n<ul>\n<li>Flash frozen right after harvest to lock-in all valuable nutrients</li>\n<li>Ready to eat in less than 10 Minutes</li>\n<li>100% plant-powered, 0% artificial flavours</li>\n<li>Shipped nationwide with next-day express delivery</li>\n<li>Produced in northern Germany</li>\n<li>Sustainably packaged & CO2 neutral</li>\n</ul>\nIf you\u2019re excited about the opportunity to shape our company and drive explosive growth, apply! Working with us means taking ownership from day one and giving everything for our mission to make a meaningful and sustainable impact.\n<br><br>\nAre you up for the challenge?\n<br><br>\nPlease submit your complete application below including your earliest starting date and salary expectation."}
{"company_name": "Teraki GmbH", "job_title": "Point Cloud Data Science Intern", "job_description": "Teraki is a Berlin-based, tech-driven company enabling true low-latency mobility by solving the big-data problem for autonomous driving.\n<br><br>\nWe stand for innovation in the rapidly developing connected car, self-driving, and 3D mapping worlds. Teraki provides data reduction and data processing solutions for Automotive (IoT) applications which enable the launch of new applications by reducing costs. With that we help our customers in the challenges that are posed by the data to be computed in (connected) cars for all sensors, video and 3D point cloud data. Teraki\u2019s algorithms are suited to improve the quality of data to meet the strict safety criteria of automotive applications. As a side effect, less data needs to be acquired and less hardware has to be deployed to maintain the strict requirements of automotive hardware.\n<br><br>\nThis combination makes it the best (and often the only) available solution for embedded use cases. We serve the OEM, Tier-1 and Aftermarket (Fleet-management, Telematics) by technically and economically enabling use cases such as Predictive Maintenance, UBI, Fleet-management, Telematics and Autonomous Driving. We focus on the B2B market. i.e. OEM, Tier1\u2019s and Aftermarket players.\n<br><br>\nTasks\n<br><br>\n<ul>\n<li>Benchmark the performance and capabilities\u202fof various point cloud-based segmentation techniques in Python and C++</li>\n<li>Contribute to the development of a path-planning stack</li>\n</ul>\nRequirements\n<br><br>\n<ul>\n<li>Student in mathematics, computer science, engineering, or physics</li>\n<li>Excellent mathematical skills, particularly in Linear Algebra</li>\n<li>Very good C++ and Cmake background</li>\n<li>Good Python background and experience with Tensorflow</li>\n<li>Strong verbal and written English skills (English is the working language, German is not required)</li>\n<li>Experience with Linux</li>\n</ul>\n<b>The ideal candidate would also have experience with:</b><br>\n<ul>\n<li>Sensor fusion</li>\n<li>Point cloud processing algorithms</li>\n<li>Machine learning</li>\n<li>Compression algorithms</li>\n</ul>\nBenefits\n<br><br>\n<ul>\n<li>The chance to immerse yourself in autonomous driving, with tasks from embedded design to machine learning</li>\n<li>To work closely with world class European and American companies</li>\n<li>To work in a dynamic start-up environment in the heart of Berlin, and to share insights with an international team spread across Europe and the US</li>\n<li>To work in a small, but highly motivated, multidisciplinary, multicultural team with flat hierarchies.</li>\n<li>Free public transport around within Berlin and free German classes</li>\n<li>The chance to be closely mentored by 3 Senior Data Scientists</li>\n</ul>\n"}
{"company_name": "ADEAL Systems GmbH", "job_title": "Data Scientist mit Engineering Interesse (w/m/d)", "job_description": "<p>Die ADEAL Systems GmbH (ADEAL = <i>Agile Data Engineering and AnaLytics</i>) bietet innovative Data Engineering und Analytics Dienstleistungen f\u00fcr Unternehmen an, die nach <i>digitaler Transformation</i> streben. Du m\u00f6chtest gerne an aktuellen Technologien und Verfahren des <i>Data Engineerings & Machine Learning</i> arbeiten und Aufgaben in modernen Cloud Infrastrukturen nachgehen? Du gestaltest gerne <i>Data Analytics</i> L\u00f6sungen und m\u00f6chtest Dich im Bereich <i>Big Data</i> weiterentwickeln?</p><p>Dann komme zu uns ins Team und bringe Deine Ideen mit ein! Wir suchen einen</p><p><b>Data Scientist </b><b>mit starkem Engineering Interesse</b>(*)</p><p>Festanstellung, Vollzeit, Remote</p><p><b>Unser Angebot: </b></p><ul><li>Keine Standortbindung bzw. die M\u00f6glichkeit remote zu arbeiten</li><li>Technisches Equipment (Laptop und Mobiltelefon etc.)</li><li>Verschiedene Weiterbildungsm\u00f6glichkeiten</li><li>Regelm\u00e4\u00dfiges Coaching & viel Gestaltungsfreiheit</li><li>Flexibilit\u00e4t bei weiteren Ideen von Dir</li></ul><p><b>Darauf kannst du dich freuen: </b></p><ul><li>Je nach Erfahrungshintergrund verantwortest Du die Konzeption und Implementierung neuer Data Science Use Cases</li><li>Unter Verwendung moderner Machine Learning und Deep Learning Verfahren beantwortest Du verschiedenste Fragestellungen unserer Kunden und leitest daraus Handlungsempfehlungen ab</li><li>Du analysierst die Daten unserer Kunden nach Trends und Mustern und hilfst damit bei der Optimierung ihrer Gesch\u00e4ftsprozesse</li><li>Aufbau von Big Data und IT Infrastrukturen in Projekten</li><li>Erarbeitung von innovativen Ans\u00e4tzen im Bereich Data und Software Engineering</li></ul><p><b>In einigen dieser Punkte findest du dich wieder: </b></p><ul><li>Abgeschlossenes Studium in den sog. MINT-F\u00e4chern</li><li>Du hast Dich - in Studium oder Praxis - schon intensiv mit maschinellen Lernverfahren wie der Clusteranalyse, Neuronalen Netzen oder Random Forest besch\u00e4ftigt</li><li>Du hast Kenntnisse einer oder mehrerer Programmiersprachen (z.B. Python, R, Scala, Java)</li><li>Erfahrungen oder Interesse an Frameworks zur Batch- und Streaming-Verarbeitung (Apache Spark & Kafka) sind von Vorteil, aber kein Muss</li><li>Du hast Grundkenntnisse oder Interesse an Big Data & Cloud Themen wie z.B. Hadoop, Elasticsearch, AWS, Azure, GCP</li><li>Eine ausgepr\u00e4gte Hands-On-Mentalit\u00e4t zeichnet dich aus und du arbeitest dich gerne in neue Technologien ein</li><li>Du bringst Erfahrungen im agilen Umfeld (Scrum/Kanban) mit</li><li>Sehr gute Deutschkenntnisse & gute Englischkenntnisse</li></ul><p><b>Kontakt: </b></p><p>Wir freuen uns auf Deine Bewerbung. Fragen beantwortet gerne:</p><p>Boris K\u00f6nig</p><p>E-Mail: team[a]adeal-systems.com</p><p>Telefon: +49 (0)1520-1389306</p><p><b>(*): w/m/d</b> \u2013 Dein Geschlecht spielt keine Rolle, ebenso deine Gesinnung, Religionszugeh\u00f6rigkeit oder eine etwaige Behinderung. Uns ist dein Interesse an der T\u00e4tigkeit wichtig und nat\u00fcrlich auch eine entsprechende Leistungsbereitschaft sowie Motivation.</p><p>Art der Stelle: Vollzeit, Festanstellung</p><p>Arbeitszeiten:</p><ul><li>Montag bis Freitag</li></ul><p>Leistungen:</p><ul><li>Empfehlungsprogramm</li><li>Firmenhandy</li><li>Flexible Arbeitszeiten</li><li>Homeoffice</li><li>Kostenlose Getr\u00e4nke</li><li>Mentoring-Programm f\u00fcr Mitarbeiter</li></ul><p>Homeoffice:</p><ul><li>Ja</li></ul>"}
{"company_name": "BTC Business Technology Consulting AG", "job_title": "Data Scientist (w/m/d)", "job_description": "<div></div><div><div><div><p><b>Das erwartet dich</b></p><ul><li><div>\nIn einem 10-k&ouml;pfigen Team, bestehend aus Data Scientists und AI Engineers, setzt du deine Machine Learning Kompetenz in verschiedenen Kundenprojekten ausgew&auml;hlter Branchen ein und realisierst dementsprechend die passenden Machine Learning Modelle f&uuml;r die jeweiligen KI Use Cases, wie bspw. Objekterkennung in Videomaterial oder Anomaliedetektion in Datenstr&ouml;men im Rahmen von Predictive IT</div></li><li><div>\nGemeinsam mit dem Team schaffst du damit sp&uuml;rbare Arbeitserleichterungen f&uuml;r unsere Kunden oder erm&ouml;glichst neue Gesch&auml;ftspotenziale, an die sie selbst vielleicht noch gar nicht gedacht haben</div></li><li><div>\nDu bist f&uuml;r Aufgaben der gesamten Data Science Verarbeitungshierarchie zust&auml;ndig, von der Datenaufbereitung &uuml;ber das Experimentieren mit Metriken und Hyperparametern bis hin zur Erstellung von produktiv nutzbaren Machine Learning Modellen</div></li><li><div>\nBei Bedarf &uuml;bernimmst du die Kommunikation der Analyseergebnisse bei unserer Kundschaft und stellst die erzielten Mehrwerte verst&auml;ndlich und pr&auml;gnant dar</div></li></ul><p></p><p><b><br>\nDas bringst du mit</b></p><ul><li><div>\nAbgeschlossenes Studium mit mathematisch-statistischem oder naturwissenschaftlichem Fokus, gepaart mit Engineering/IT-Anteil</div></li><li><div>\nVertieftes Verst&auml;ndnis von Machine Learning Methoden (bspw. Klassifikations- und Regressionsverfahren) und der dazugeh&ouml;rigen Verarbeitungshierarchie (Data Cleaning, Feature Engineering, Dataset Augmentation &amp; Enrichment, Modelling, Tuning, Visualization)</div></li><li><div>\nSicherer Umgang mit Python und den einschl&auml;gigen Bibliotheken sowie erste Erfahrungen mit AWS Cloud-Technologie (alternativ Azure oder SAP)</div></li><li><div>\nSelbstst&auml;ndigkeit und Eigeninitiative f&uuml;r die Erarbeitung individueller L&ouml;sungen im Rahmen der Kundenanforderung, inklusive beratender Funktion zur L&ouml;sungsvermittlung</div></li><li><div>\nHervorragende Sprachkenntnisse in Deutsch, ab Niveau C1</div></li><li><div>\nBereitschaft f&uuml;r gelegentliche Abstimmungen mit dem Team und f&uuml;r die Einarbeitung nach Oldenburg zu reisen</div></li></ul><p><b><br>\nDas bieten wir dir</b></p><ul><li><div>\nEinen pers&ouml;nlichen Paten f&uuml;r die Einarbeitung</div></li><li><div>\nUnbefristete Anstellung</div></li><li><div>\nGleitzeit oder Vertrauensarbeitszeit auf Basis von 40 Std./Woche oder in Teilzeit</div></li><li><div>\nHome-Office Modelle von einzelnen Tagen bis zum Full Homeoffice</div></li><li><div>\nFreir&auml;ume sowie Ruhe- und Sozialr&auml;ume f&uuml;r Co-Working, konzentriertes Arbeiten und Kaffeegespr&auml;che</div></li><li><div>\nEine Unternehmenskultur, die von gelebter Diversit&auml;t, Duzen, Dynamik und einem offenen Dialog gepr&auml;gt ist</div></li><li><div>\nEntwicklungsm&ouml;glichkeiten im Rahmen deines pers&ouml;nlichen Karrierepfads mit Soft-Skills-Trainings sowie Methoden- und Fachschulungen</div></li><li><div>\nEin umfangreiches Angebot an Sozialleistungen, z.B. unser Altersvorsorgemodell im Rahmen der Konzernzugeh&ouml;rigkeit zur EWE AG, Angebote zur Gesundheitsf&ouml;rderung und standortspezifische Angebote wie eine Kantine oder Kinderbetreuungseinrichtung</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div></div>"}
{"company_name": "Roq.ad GmbH", "job_title": "Data Science/Machine Learning Roqstar", "job_description": "<div><p>We are building a global identity resolution system for Internet marketing. We use our Machine Learning algorithm to analyze dozens of terabytes of data daily and predict device profiles for hundreds of millions of people.</p>\n<p>\nWe started out in 2015 in Berlin and Poznan. Then, we opened our office in Vilnius. Now we go to conquer the United States, and we want you to do it with us!</p><br>\n<p></p>\n<h3 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>\nYour responsibilities</b></h3>\n<ul><li>Work on design and optimization of prediction algorithms</li>\n<li>Improve our capabilities in large-scale data mining, analysis, information retrieval, data visualization, ML and AI</li>\n<li> Assist in the development of predictive algorithms to solve complex business challenges and extract information from data sets</li>\n<li> Work on data acquisition and mashuping process</li>\n<li> Support Roq.ad customers with necessary data analysis and metrics calculation</li>\n<li> Work closely with Roq.ad&rsquo;s engineering team on building and deploying a data analysis system for large data sets</li></ul><br>\n<p></p>\n<h3 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>\nWhat we expect from you</b></h3>\n<ul><li>Degree in Statistics, Applied Mathematics, Computer Science, Operations Research or equivalent</li>\n<li>Knowledge in using discrete math, linear algebra, probability and statistics to answer complex questions</li>\n<li>Experience with designing and developing Machine Learning algorithms</li>\n<li>Experience with Data Mining and Information Retrieval</li>\n<li>Experience with data visualization of large datasets, as well as data pipelines</li>\n<li>Experience with Big Data technologies, such as Hadoop (HDFS, Hive, HBase, MapReduce), Apache Spark, Spark Streaming, etc.</li>\n<li>Ability to rapidly learn new technologies</li>\n<li>Fluency in English</li></ul><br>\n<p></p>\n<h3 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>\nWhat we offer</b></h3>\n<p><b>\nAre you ready for Roq.ad?</b> You will work in an exciting and challenging environment with a strong company culture based on fast growth and transparency. You will be solving problems that affect millions of our users using the best tools and technologies. You will learn a lot along the way while working with an extremely motivated and skilled team of our engineers. You can work from home or at our Poznan office. On top of that &ndash; we will pay you a competitive salary.</p><br>\n<p></p>\n<p>\nWe are looking forward to receiving your application!</p>\n<p>\nPlease send it to jobs@roq.ad</p></div><div></div>"}
{"company_name": "Univativ GmbH", "job_title": "Werkstudent (m/w/d) Data Science", "job_description": "univativ ist ein Projekt- und Personaldienstleister, der Studenten und Absolventen spannende Jobs bei renommierten Unternehmen bietet. Deine Karriere ist unsere Mission, denn Deine Entwicklung liegt uns am Herzen.\n<br><br>\nDu studierst Informatik und verf\u00fcgst \u00fcber fortgeschrittene Kenntnisse in Python? Dann suchen wir Dich als Werkstudent (m/w/d) Data Science! Du programmierst Skripte zur Datenauswertung und optimierst die Datenbank.\n<br><br>\nUnser Kunde ist eine Unternehmensberatung mit dem Schwerpunkt in der Analyse und Optimierung der Abl\u00e4ufe und Strukturen von vorrangig kleinen und mittleren Unternehmen. Wenn Du Dich in der Stellenbeschreibung wiederfindest, freuen wir uns auf Deine Bewerbung!\n<br><br>\nAufgaben\n<br><br>\n<ul>\n<li>Programmierung von Skripten</li>\n<li>Durchf\u00fchrung von Datenauswertungen</li>\n<li>Optimierung der Datenbank</li>\n</ul>\nQualifikation\n<br><br>\n<ul>\n<li>Laufendes Studium der Informatik oder einer vergleichbaren Fachrichtung</li>\n<li>Fortgeschrittene Erfahrung im Umgang mit Python</li>\n<li>Verhandlungssichere Deutschkenntnisse</li>\n<li>Eine strukturierte Arbeitsweise</li>\n</ul>\nBenefits\n<br><br>\n<ul>\n<li>R\u00fcckmeldung innerhalb k\u00fcrzester Zeit</li>\n<li>Networking in verschiedenen Branchen</li>\n<li>Betreuung durch einen pers\u00f6nlichen Talent Coach</li>\n<li>Ein dynamisches, innovatives Arbeitsumfeld</li>\n<li>Start: baldm\u00f6glichst</li>\n<li>Laufzeit bis 28.02.2022</li>\n<li>20 Std./Woche</li>\n</ul>\n"}
{"company_name": "Simplifa GmbH", "job_title": "Data Scientist IoT Sensor Data (Student) (m/f/d)", "job_description": "<div></div><div><h2 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>Data Scientist IoT Sensor Data (Student) (m/f/d)</b></h2>\n<h6 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>Intern / Student, Part-time &middot; Berlin\n</b></h6><p></p><div><div><div><h5 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>Your mission</b></h5>\n<div><div><div><div>Analyzing high frequency sensor data from IoT-Devices that are installed on elevators</div><div>\nFind root causes for elevator breakdowns and incidence in data</div><div>\nWorking together with elevator technicians to analyze the data</div></div></div>\nSupport the machine learning team in improving ML-models\n</div></div><div><h5 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>Your profile</b></h5>\n<div><div><div><div><b>Must have:</b></div></div><div><div>\nBachelor&rsquo;s degree in data science, sciences, engineering or similar</div><div>\nExperience in time series and signal processing</div></div></div><div><div><div>\nGood understanding of probability and statistics</div><div>\nExperience with jupyter notebook</div><div>\nGood understanding of physics and dynamical systems</div><div>\nAdvanced programming skills in Python</div><p>\nUnderstanding of deep learning methodologies<br>\nEnglish and German at least level C1</p></div></div><div><div><div><b><br>\nNice </b><b>to</b><b> </b><b>have</b><b>:</b></div></div><div><div>\nExperience with IoT and distributed systems</div><div>\nKnowledge of processing audio data</div><div>\nKnowledge of processing inertial sensor data</div></div></div><div><div><div>\nKnowledge of Bayesian inference and concepts</div><div>\nKnowledge of machine learning tools and platforms such as Tensorflow, Keras, Pytorch, etc.</div><div>\nExperience with collaborative development tools such as Jira, Confluence, GitLab&hellip;</div></div></div><br>\nRemote work is not possible, the location of work is Berlin\n</div></div><div>Apply for this position\n</div><div><h5 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>About us</b></h5>\n<div>Who we are Simplifa GmbH structures, optimises and manages elevator portfolios on behalf of the owners and positions itself as a neutral liaison between the owner's representatives and the elevator service companies. Each elevator in Simplifa's elevator management system is technically inspected at the beginning, the current condition is assessed, and the inventory documentation is digitally recorded. The elevator is completely recorded with the help of 360&deg; photos &amp; videos and is then virtually reconstructed.\n</div></div></div><div>Apply for this position\n</div></div><div><div><h5 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>Your application!</b></h5>\n<div>We appreciate your interest in Simplifa GmbH. Please fill in the following short form. Should you have any difficulties in uploading your files, please contact us by email.\n</div></div><div><div><div>Name *\n</div></div><p></p><div>Email *\n</div><p></p><div>Phone *\n</div><p></p><div><div>Available from *\n</div></div><p></p><div><div>Expected salary *\n</div></div><p></p><div>Documents\n<p>Please upload your CV, recent certificates as well as a brief cover letter (in total max. 20 MB).</p>\n<div><div>CV *\n<div><div>Click to select multiple files or use drag-and-drop\n</div></div></div><div>Other\n<div><div>Click to select multiple files or use drag-and-drop\n</div></div></div></div></div><p></p><div>*\n </div><p></p><div><div>I hereby confirm that I have read and understood the Data privacy statement.*\n</div></div><div>Uploading document. Please wait.\n</div><div><div><p>Send application\n</p></div><div><p>Cancel</p></div></div></div></div></div>"}
{"company_name": "idalab GmbH", "job_title": "Student Trainee Data/AI Consulting in Life Science & Health (x/f/m)", "job_description": "<div>PLEASE NOTE OUR RECRUITING POLICY DURING CORONA\n<p>\nOur recruiting will not be interrupted. Applications are processed, online tests are sent, video interviews are conducted, challenges are sent, interview days take place in our office with respect to hygiene regulations.</p>\n<p>\nWe look forward to receiving your application!</p>\nYOUR START IN ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE &amp; DATA SCIENCE CONSULTING\n<p><b>\nArtificial intelligence needs generalists: that is what the Junior Associate Programme is about</b></p>\n<p>\nAs a candidate in our Junior Associate Programme, we will train you in the field of Data Science &amp; Artificial Intelligence Consulting with a focus on Life Science and Healthcare topics. At the beginning, you will work as a Student Assistant together with experienced colleagues on projects for our demanding clients and quickly take responsibility for your own work packages. On your way to becoming a Junior Associate, you will analyze data, design presentations, develop mathematical models, conduct interviews, invent algorithms, research information, design strategies and moderate workshops - always in direct personal contact with our clients, as well as accompanied and supported by your mentor and our self-developed, comprehensive training modules.</p>\nYOUR PROFILE\n<p><b>\nYou are passionate about your studies &ndash; what exactly you are studying is of secondary importance.</b></p>\n<ul>\n<li>You are currently studying for a Master's degree, with very good academic results, in a subject with a high quantitative component (e.g. economics, physics, engineering, empirical social sciences, mathematics, computer science, psychology, statistics, cognitive neuroscience).</li>\n<li>You have basic experience with data analysis and statistics as well as practical experience with relevant software tools (R, Python, SQL, etc.); ideally also experience in programming.</li>\n<li>Ideally, you have already gained some work experience in relevant internships in business, preferably in a challenging environment such as management consulting.</li>\n<li>You are a long-term thinker and the prospect of receiving sound practical training in parallel to your studies, as well as getting to know the team in which you will take your first steps as a young professional, is very appealing to you.</li>\n<li>You have 20h / week to work at idalab, in the semester break even more.</li>\n<li>You are open to intern with us for at least six weeks during the first six months of your employment with us.</li>\n<li>You are fluent in written and spoken German and English.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><b>Your drive: Designing solutions, with full personal responsibility</b></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Passion for detail-oriented hands-on work with data while keeping in mind the big picture</li>\n<li>Outstanding analytical and conceptual-creative skills: Ambiguity excites you, clarity is what you are constantly creating</li>\n<li>Strong communication skills, empathy and enjoyment of personal contact with a wide variety of people</li>\n<li>Commitment, energy, and inner striving for excellence and professionalism</li>\n<li>Always result-oriented: The focus is on customer value, creatively overcoming hurdles of all kinds gives you pleasure</li>\n<li>Desire for service, externally as well as internally</li>\n<li>You enjoy continuous learning, because no situation or project is like another</li>\n<li>Modesty, humor and an authentic personality</li>\n<li>Entrepreneurial drive to contribute to developing a small company</li>\n</ul>WE OFFER\n<ul><li>A structured training as a Data Science Consultant with focus on Life Science within our Junior Associate Program, which includes comprehensive training in Methdodology, Technical Skills, Strategic Thinking, Effective Communication, as well as Professional Working Style. You will receive comprehensive support from our entire team, as well as a dedicated mentor who will keep an eye on your training goals and continuously pursue them together with you.</li>\n<li>With appropriate performance and commitment, you will be promoted to Junior Associate with the prospect of a full-time transfer to our Associate Program at the end of your studies, the goal of which is the development to Senior Associate.</li>\n<li>Challenging, highly innovative and strategically relevant projects for demanding clients with direct contact to top management.</li>\n<li>Growing focus on healthcare, biotech and life science topics</li>\n<li>High level of personal responsibility and a team with a positive attitude towards risky decisions, new ways and own mistakes</li>\n<li>Open, friendly atmosphere and a colorful mix of genuine personalities at eye level; neither streamlines nor elbows</li>\n<li>Participation in biannual retreats (Thursday - Sunday), with a focus on training, strategy update and business development</li>\n<li>High quality work equipment and an hourly wage of 16 euros + annual profit sharing.</li>\n<li>After promotion from Student Assistant to Junior Associate (usually happens during the time as working student): 18,50 Euro</li>\n</ul>\n<p><b>We develop outstanding talents into co-owners</b></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Performance and commitment required very fast development opportunities: after the end of your studies via the associate program up to co-ownership (partner) with great freedom to develop your own topics, markets and relationships.</li>\n<li>A wide range of creative opportunities in a young company</li>\n<li>Working predominantly in the Berlin office, but traveling at any time and at short notice for appointments with clients on site (Europe and USA)</li>\n<li>Transparent annual profit sharing for the entire team, from working student to managing director</li>\n</ul>ABOUT US\n<p>\nWe are a small independent Artificial Intelligence consulting company. We grow organically with our clients and colleagues. Our focus is on issues in the areas of health care, biotech and life science.</p>\n<p>\nWe are convinced that for a sustainable positive contribution of Artificial Intelligence a generalist approach is indispensable: the integrated consideration of mathematical-algorithmic details and holistic strategy.</p>\nGET TO KNOW US\n<p>\nIn times without a global pandemic: A good opportunity to get to know us and to get an insight into our working atmosphere is the regularly held public idalab seminar.</p>\n<p>\nWe are also happy to arrange an informal meeting with future colleagues in advance. Just contact us, we are looking forward to speaking with you.\n</p>OUR APPLICATION PROCESS\n<p>\nOur application procedure follows a structured process. An online test asks for basic knowledge of mathematics and statistics. In a telephone interview, we would like to learn more about your motivation and your ability to explain complex models in an accessible way. Our challenge will give you the opportunity to demonstrate your conceptual and technical skills. Finally, on the interview day, you will present the results of your challenge to the team and have the opportunity to get to know your future colleagues in a total of three individual interviews.</p>\n<p>\nPlease apply with your cover letter, CV and a proof of previous examination achievements (including grades) via the career page of our homepage. PLEASE NOTE THAT INCOMPLETE APPLICATIONS WILL NOT BE CONSIDERED. We look forward to hearing from you and are eager to receive your application!</p>\nCONTACT\n<p>\nPlease apply exclusively via our career page, as we are unable to process applications by mail for data protection reasons. However, if you have any questions about this job posting or the application process, please feel free to contact Marlene Sch&ouml;bel directly at:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>marlene.schoebel@idalab.de</li>\n<li>+49 (30) 814 513-24</li></ul></div>"}
{"company_name": "Forto GmbH", "job_title": "Internship Data Science (f/m/d)", "job_description": "Our Company\n<br>Simplifying global trade has been Forto\u2019s mission from day one. Forto stands for scalable and sustainable logistics technologies that allows users to own their entire supply chain. A one-stop-shop and single face to the customer that would cover the entire process chain from quotation, booking, document management, track and trace all the way to proactive exception handling and supply chain data analytics. A growing team of over 450 technology and logistics experts at ten locations, together with financing totalling over USD 100 million, forms the basis for further growth.\n<br><br>\nYour Role\n<br>As part of the product team, you transform Forto into a data-driven organization; driving the company\u2019s product vision forward by harnessing the existing data to get reliable, scalable, and explainable insights to both internal and external stakeholders.\n<br><br>\nYou will\n<br><br>\n<ul>\n<li>Develop and test new features for existing machine learning models to help our customers in several ways to improve their shipments\u2019 reliability, performance, and prevent issues from happening proactively.</li>\n<li>Scale and automate machine learning pipelines to leverage computational resources, instead of one-off solutions.</li>\n<li>Engineer new Machine Learning features and assess their performance for future shipments.</li>\n<li>Constantly challenge the status quo and get healthy predictions for the future.</li>\n<li>Learn to deal with label delay and get real world experience on spotting and preventing overfitting.</li>\n<li>Find data quality issues and collaborate with data engineers to improve data quality.</li>\n</ul>\nWhat you bring\n<br><br>\n<ul>\n<li>You have applied machine learning knowledge and experience.</li>\n<li>You have strong skills with some of the languages and technologies we use: Python, SQL, Pandas, vectorized computation.</li>\n<li>You have a good understanding of statistics.</li>\n<li>Curiosity, passion for data, continuous learning, and personal growth.</li>\n<li>Working proficiency and communication skills in verbal and written English.</li>\n<li>Available for 6+ months of internship</li>\n</ul>\nWhy Us - You can look forward to\n<br><br>\n<ul>\n<li>Personal & Professional Development: Through strong ownership from the first day you will experience a steep learning curve, grow on a professional level and take the next steps to being an Expert or People Lead.</li>\n<li>Impact: We are leading the digital transformation of a whole industry and share a high awareness for environmental issues on all levels especially supported by our management.</li>\n<li>Team: Join a team of over 30 nationalities and different backgrounds from Tech, Logistics, Business and more. What really matters to us is a caring and welcoming environment where we embrace uniqueness and celebrate diversity.</li>\n<li>Working culture: Experience a company culture where we work on eye level, decisions are made quickly and knowledge sharing, as well as mentoring is on our daily agenda.</li>\n</ul>\nCulture\n<br><b>Check out our video to see what it is like to work at Forto:</b> https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g4A7kaUaN4w.\n<br><br>\nAt Forto we don\u2019t just accept differences \u2014 we celebrate them, support them and cultivate them to the benefit of our employees, products and our communities. Forto is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer."}
{"company_name": "WBS TRAINING AG ", "job_title": "Instructor (m/f/d) Data Science", "job_description": "<div></div><div><div><div><div><h2 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>We empower people through education. Join us!\n</b></h2><p>THIS IS US. WBS GRUPPE.\n</p></div><p>WBS GRUPPE is one of the leading education providers in Germany. We offer subsidised further vocational training and retraining (WBS TRAINING), in-house training (WBS AKADEMIE), professional programs in the fields of health, nursing and social services (WBS SCHOOL), boot camps for software developers (WBS CODING SCHOOL) as well as recruitment of trainees and skilled workers from abroad (WBS RECRUITING INTERNATIONAL). Thanks to our digital and flexible learning formats, we are able to convey excellent qualifications, self-competence and practical expertise. In this way we improve the job and career opportunities of our customers and support companies in finding and promoting highly qualified specialists. Be part of it!\n</p></div><div><div><p>INSTRUCTOR (M/F/D) DATA SCIENCE</p>\n<div></div><div><div><div><p>BERLIN / REMOTE\n</p></div></div></div><div></div><div><div><p>08/30/2021</p>\n</div></div><div></div><div><div><p>FULL TIME AS A FREELANCER</p>\n</div></div></div></div><p></p><div><div><div><p>YOUR TASKS\n </p><p>As a Data Science Instructor (m/f/d) of WBS CODING SCHOOL, you are responsible for the learning success and experience of our students.<br>\nIn our 15-week Data Science program, you will teach online for 12 weeks and then meet your students for the last 3 weeks at our Coding Campus in Berlin. You will run regular workshops for our participants and support them in the event of challenges.<br>\nYour tasks:</p><br>\n<ul><li>You are responsible for conducting workshops, live coding sessions and other learning events (lessons take place 9:00 am&ndash; 6:00 pm, Mon - Fr.).</li>\n<li>You motivate our participants and coach them according to their needs.</li>\n<li>Together with our Product Managers and our instructor team, you will continue to develop our curriculum to ensure the continuous improvement of our courses).</li>\n</ul></div></div><div><div><p>YOUR STRENGTHS\n</p><p>You are looking for a flexible working environment in a young and dynamic team and you are excited to introduce young talents to this cutting-edge tech-branch. For this, we would like the following expertise from you:</p><br>\n<ul><li>3+ years of experience as a professional data scientist\n<br>\n</li><li>You have extensive experience with SQL.</li>\n<li>You have experience with Python for Data Analysis (Numpy, Pandas, Matplotlib &amp; Seaborn, beautifulsoup, requests&hellip;) and Machine Learning (Scikit-Learn, Keras).</li>\n<li>Ideally, you have some experience with Cloud Computing (AWS - IAM, S3, EC2, Lambda, RDS).</li>\n<li>You are capable of performing A/B tests and are familiar with the main concepts around Statistical Inference.</li>\n<li>You respond empathetically your students&rsquo; needs.</li>\n<li>You love to share your knowledge and experience with the students and the team.</li>\n<li>You are a self-starter and enjoy working independently .</li>\n<li>You are highly proficient in English, both spoken and written.</li>\n<li>You are available from August 30th &ndash; December 10th 2021 and can arrange to come to Berlin for the last three weeks of the program.</li>\n</ul></div></div></div><p></p><p>BENEFITS\n</p><p></p><div><div><div><h3 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>Contribute.\n</b></h3><div>Whether it's working on different projects, submitting your ideas through our Trendbox or using our feedback tool. Help us shape change and be part of the development.\n</div></div></div><p></p><div><div><h3 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>Learn.\n</b></h3><div>Stay curious. Plenty of further education programs and 3 paid training days per year are waiting for you.\n</div></div></div><p></p><div><div><h3 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>Work-life-balance.\n</b></h3><div>30 working days of annual vacation, various working time models, a sabbatical or work from home. Stay flexible with us!\n</div></div></div></div><p></p><div><div><div><h3 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>Digital work.\n</b></h3><div>Stay connected with all your colleagues across the country: in virtual learning formats, digital sports activities and through digitalised working processes.\n</div></div></div><p></p><div><div><h3 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>Purpose.\n</b></h3><div>Common Good Certification, sustainable food and travel, fund-raising campaigns or developing your individual potential. Work with us in a meaningful and socially oriented way.\n</div></div></div><p></p><div><div><h3 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>Feel good.\n</b></h3><div>A friendly atmosphere, free wellness programs, a job bike and mutual trust. Feel good with us in every way!\n</div></div></div></div><p></p><div><div><div><p>WE ARE LOOKING FORWARD TO YOUR ONLINE APPLICATION!</p>\n<p>Please enter your salary expectations and your earliest possible entry date.\n</p><p>The pronouns used in this job advertisement include all genders (male, female, diverse).</p>\n<p></p><p>With your application, you agree to the further processing and storage of your data until the application process is completed.\n</p><p><b>APPLY NOW</b></p>\n <br>\n<p><b>PDF\n</b></p></div></div></div><p></p><h3 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>YOUR CONTACT TO THE WBS GROUP\n</b></h3><div><p>LENA ERNST\n</p><div>Bereiche: WBS CODING SCHOOL | SPRACHEN | LOGISTIK<br>\nFON 030 70193452</div></div></div></div><p></p>"}
{"company_name": "DATANOMIQ GmbH", "job_title": "Data Science Trainee", "job_description": "<div><p>DATANOMIQ ist der erste deutsche Anbieter f&uuml;r Beratung und Dienstleistungen, der Data Analytics ganzheitlich versteht und anbietet. Von klassischer Business Intelligence &uuml;ber Process Mining bis hin zu Data Science und Deep Learning bestreiten wir die Daten(r)evolution aus allen Perspektiven. Wir sind eine innovative und ambitionierte Company mit datenbegeisterten Kollegen. Was uns t&auml;glich antreibt ist es, herausragende L&ouml;sungen f&uuml;r anspruchsvolle, datenbasierte Probleme zu entwickeln. Bei DATANOMIQ erleben wir das Morgen schon heute. Vielleicht bald mit Dir.</p>\n<p>\nAufgrund unseres angestrebten Wachstums sowie der kontinuierlichen Erweiterung unseres L&ouml;sungs- und Service-Portfolios suchen wir nach motivierten und engagierten Talenten f&uuml;r unsere junge, erfolgreiche Mannschaft. Werde Teil eines sympathischen und zum permanenten Lernen bereiten Teams durch deinen Einstieg als Data Analyst f&uuml;r Process Mining.</p>\n<p><b>\nDeine Aufgaben</b></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Unterst&uuml;tzung bei Projekten f&uuml;r Data Science, Business Intelligence oder Process Mining</li>\n<li>Unterst&uuml;tzung beim Erstellen von KPI-Dashboards und Prozessanalysen</li>\n<li>Explorative Datenanalyse und Datenvisualisierung</li>\n<li>Erstellung von technischen Dokumentationen und Tutorials</li>\n<li>Diverse Projektbezogene analytische und kommunikative Aufgaben</li>\n</ul>\n<p><b>Dein Profil:</b></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Erfolgreich abgeschlossenes Studium in den F&auml;chern Physik, Ingenieurwesen, (Wirtschafts-)Informatik, (Wirtschafts-)Mathematik oder Wirtschaftswissenschaften mit starkem quantitativen Fokus bzw. Statistik</li>\n<li>Erfahrung im Umgang mit BI-Tools und Programmiersprachen wie VBA oder Python.</li>\n<li>Gute SQL-Kenntnisse</li>\n<li>Gute Statistikkenntnisse</li>\n<li>Verhandlungssichere Englisch- und Deutschkenntnisse</li>\n<li>Hohes Ma&szlig; an Eigeninitiative und Zielorientierung</li>\n<li>Bereitschaft f&uuml;r intensives Lernen und Einarbeiten mit eigenem Antrieb!</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Der Wechsel vom Data Science Trainee zum vollen Data Scientist, Data Engineer oder Data Analyst ist m&ouml;glich und eingeplant.</p>\n<p>\nWenn Du gerne in einem dynamischen Umfeld mit flachen Hierarchien und kurzen Entscheidungswegen arbeiten m&ouml;chtest, sende uns bitte Deine aussagekr&auml;ftige Bewerbung mit dem Stichwort &bdquo;Data Science Trainee&ldquo; unter Angabe Deiner Gehaltsvorstellung sowie m&ouml;glichen Eintrittstermins an jobs@datanomiq.de.</p>\n<p>\nWir freuen uns darauf, Dich kennenzulernen!</p></div>"}
{"company_name": "Clariness", "job_title": "Working Student/Part-time (m/f/d) Data Quality", "job_description": "<p>(Hamburg or Berlin, Partime or Working Student, 20 h/week max, permanent)<br/>Text annotation is an essential component in training automated text processing techniques, such as deep learning, and requires meticulous attention to detail. We seek individuals with outstanding interest in the scientific field/medical science and attention to detail to support the Data Solutions Team as <b>Working Student/Part-time role (max. 20 hours/week)</b> in order to assist the annotation of medical text to establish an automated information-extraction pipeline. Once trained, you will work under limited supervision, collaborating closely with scientists and other support groups within Clariness.</p><p><b>What you'll do: </b></p><ul><li>Use an annotation tool for making annotations (Prodigy or Doccano)</li><li>Correctly identify and annotate scientific or medical terms</li><li>Able to communicate with the medical doctor/scientific staff (on-site/off-site) if there is ambiguity in the annotations</li><li>Contribute feedback to help further develop the annotation software and workflows</li><li>Review/correct existing automatically or manually generated annotations</li></ul><p><b>Who you are: </b></p><ul><li>Educational background (BSc or MSc) in Cellular Biology, Neuroscience, Biomedical Engineering, Medicine, or any related fields.</li><li>Familiarity with Mesh (Medical Subject Headings)</li><li>Correctly identify, analyze, and collect relevant data from texts as instructed by scientific staff</li><li>Ability to perform repetitive tasks while paying close attention to detail</li><li>Experience with Google Spreadsheets or Microsoft Excel</li><li>Good organizational skills</li><li>Ability to work independently yet assimilate well into a team</li><li>Proactive, resourceful, and able to generate results according to defined deadlines</li></ul><p><b>Good to Have: </b></p><ul><li>Experience with Python, or other programming languages</li><li>Experience working with databases and/or interacting with software developers</li></ul><p><b>What</b>* we<b>* offer</b></p><ul><li>A varied and exciting job with a lot of personal responsibility in an international company, where you can develop and expand your skills</li><li>A secure workplace with many possibilities and room for your own ideas</li><li>A versatile field of activity and challenging projects</li><li>Professional and personal development opportunities</li><li>Competitive salary and benefits</li><li>Flexible working hours and mobile working (home office)</li><li>Make an impact in healthcare - The speed of bringing needed medical innovation to market still depends on the duration of <i>clinical</i> trials. By globally lowering the barrier for access to <i>clinical</i> trials and increasing the chances to find a treatment for patients, we accelerate medical innovation.</li></ul><p><b>Have we sparked your interest?</b><br/>Would you like to become part of our dynamic, curious, and international culture with plenty of room for your ideas and creativity in an inspiring atmosphere? If so, we look forward to receiving your application with details of your desired salary and possible starting date, preferably via our application portal.</p><p>Contact person:<br/>Ms. Colette Rollin<br/>Interim Recruiting Manager<br/>Phone: +49 (151) 50 42 09 12<br/>recruiting@clariness.com</p><p>Clariness GmbH will treat the above information strictly confidential and will especially observe the applicable provisions of the applicable data protection laws. Further information about the use of the applicant data, you will find in the data protection declaration online at https://www.clariness.com/privacy-policy/</p><p>Job Type: Part-time</p>"}
{"company_name": "Yelp Inc.", "job_title": "Data Scientist (Remote)", "job_description": "<div><div>At Yelp, it&rsquo;s our mission to connect people with great local businesses. Yelp&rsquo;s unique dataset contains billions of interactions between users and local businesses around the globe, from a user reviewing a neighborhood coffee shop to requesting a repair quote with a photo of a leaky faucet. Data Scientists at Yelp work to make sense of these interactions to deliver impactful analyses and products to our users, business partners, and the general public.</div><div></div><div><br>\nThe Data Science team performs analyses, builds models, and designs experiments that directly impact Yelp&rsquo;s business and users. Our centralized team is the most wide-ranging consumer of data at Yelp, adept at tasks from modeling content growth and user behavior to sharing insights about the health of local economies. With varied backgrounds and expertise, we strive for learning and growth in a collaborative environment.</div><div></div><div><br>\nWe&rsquo;d love to have you apply, even if you don't feel you meet every single requirement in this posting. At Yelp, we&rsquo;re looking for great people, not just those who simply check off all the boxes.</div><div></div><h3 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b><br>\nWhere You Come In:</b></h3><ul><li>\nSeveral years of experience as a data scientist and industry experience in a quantitative role</li><li>\nFluency with SQL and Python for data analysis</li><li>\nSolid understanding of statistical inference, experimental design, and analysis</li><li>\nEnthusiasm for clean code and sharing reproducible results</li><li>\nCommunication skills to work with partners on product, engineering, and sales teams</li><li>\nAn eye for great data visualization (Matplotlib, Plotly, Tableau, Power BI, Mode, or Looker)</li></ul><h3 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b><br>\nWhat it Takes to Succeed:</b></h3><ul><li>\nBased in or willing to relocate within the United Kingdom or Germany</li><li>\nDefine key metrics to track Yelp&rsquo;s performance and inform product decisions</li><li>\nAssess and frame questions from partners into actionable deliverables</li><li>\nDesign, execute, and analyze complex experiments impacting millions of users</li><li>\nDevise and evaluate models for diverse business needs, such as identifying growth opportunities, demonstrating impact of advertisements, and matching consumers to businesses</li><li>\nOwn analyses from start to finish and communicate key insights to stakeholders</li><li>\nShare your technical skills to develop and maintain high-quality, reusable analysis tools</li></ul><h3 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b><br>\nWhat You&rsquo;ll Get:\n</b></h3><ul><li>Full responsibility for projects from day one, an awesome team, and a dynamic work environment</li><li>\nCompetitive salary with equity in the company, a pension scheme, and an optional employee stock purchase program</li><li>\n25 days paid holiday initially (rising to 29 with service), plus one floating holiday</li><li>\nPrivate health insurance, including dental and vision</li><li>\nFlexible working hours and meeting-free Wednesdays</li><li>\nRegular 3-day Hackathons and weekly learning groups, always with interesting topics</li><li>\nOpportunities to participate in digital events and conferences</li><li>\n&euro;58 per month toward any wellness activity of your choice</li><li>\nQuarterly team offsites</li></ul><div><i><br>\nYelp values diversity. We&rsquo;re proud to be an equal opportunity employer and consider qualified applicants without regard to Race/Ethnic Origin, Sex, Religion/Belief, Disability, Age, Sexual Orientation.<br>\n</i></div><div></div><br>\n<div><i>Note: Yelp does not accept agency resumes. Please do not forward resumes to any recruiting alias or employee. Yelp is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.</i></div></div>"}
{"company_name": "Informationstechnikzentrum Bund", "job_title": "Data Scientist (w/m/d)", "job_description": "<div><div><div><div><p>Standort Berlin Ilmenau Hamburg\n</p></div></div><div><div><p>Arbeitszeit Vollzeit und Teilzeit\n</p></div><div><p>Laufbahn gehobener Dienst\n</p></div><div><p>T&auml;tigkeitsfeld IT-Architektur\n</p></div></div><div><div><p>Anstellungsdauer Unbefristet\n</p></div><div><p>Bewerbungsfrist 26. Juli 2021\n</p></div><div><p>Bund.de Kennziffer Z7-P1464-3-21/21-e</p></div></div></div></div>\n<br><div><div><p>Bonn - 2. Juli 2021\n</p><div><h2 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>Ihre Rolle</b></h2>\n<p>Das Themenfelder K&uuml;nstliche Intelligenz (KI) und Business Intelligence (BI) spielen auch in der &ouml;ffentlichen Verwaltung eine gro&szlig;e Rolle. Werden Sie Teil eines aufstrebenden Spezialbereichs der Softwareentwicklung innerhalb des ITZBund, damit wir unsere Kunden im Rahmen der begonnenen Digitalisierungsoffensive der Bundesregierung z.B. im Bereich Betrugsbek&auml;mpfung noch effizienter unterst&uuml;tzen k&ouml;nnen.</p>\n<p>Folgende Aufgaben erwarten Sie:</p>\n<ul><li>Beratung der Kunden in unterschiedlichen Projektphasen</li><li>\nTransfer fachlicher in analytische Fragestellungen im Kontext von Kundenprojekten</li><li>\nAuswahl und Einsatz geeigneter BI-Systeme oder Maschine Learning- Methoden</li><li>\nErstellung von BI-Systemen und Erstellung/Training von KI-Modellen</li><li>\nDatenmanagement</li><li>\nBeauftragung und Einrichtung der Entwicklungsumgebungen und -werkzeuge</li><li>\nSicherstellung der Qualit&auml;t der Analyseergebnisse</li><li>\nDefinition von Ma&szlig;nahmen und Aktivit&auml;ten auf Basis von Datenanalysen</li><li>\nUnterst&uuml;tzung der Projektleitung / Verfahrensverantwortung</li></ul>\n</div></div><div><div><h2 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>Ihre F&auml;higkeiten</b></h2>\n<h3 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>Zwingende Anforderungen</b></h3>\n<ul><li>Sie verf&uuml;gen &uuml;ber ein erfolgreich abgeschlossenes Fachhochschul- bzw. Bachelorstudium, in den Fachrichtungen Informatik, Wirtschaftsinformatik, Mathematik, Physik, Elektrotechnik, Nachrichtentechnik oder in vergleichbaren Studieng&auml;ngen mit IT-Bezug. Dar&uuml;ber hinaus verf&uuml;gen Sie &uuml;ber mindestens dreij&auml;hrige praktische Berufserfahrung in der Informationstechnik.</li><li>\nAlternativ verf&uuml;gen Sie &uuml;ber nachgewiesene, gleichwertige F&auml;higkeiten und Erfahrungen im entsprechenden Berufsbild von mindestens 6 Jahren.</li><li>\nAls Beamtin/Beamter befinden Sie sich in der Laufbahn des gehobenen Dienstes in der BesGr. A 11 oder A 12 BBesO.</li></ul>\n<h3 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>Auswahlrelevante Kriterien</b></h3>\n<h4 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>Das bringen Sie fachlich mit:</b></h4>\n<ul><li>Gute Kenntnisse im Bereich BI und K&uuml;nstliche Intelligenz</li><li>\nGute Kenntnisse g&auml;ngiger Programmiersprachen und Bibliotheken (KI)</li><li>\nGute Kenntnisse und erste Erfahrungen in Projekten im Bereich Data Science</li><li>\nGute Kenntnisse und erste Erfahrungen in der Vermittlung und Pr&auml;sentation komplexer analytischer Zusammenh&auml;nge</li></ul>\n<h4 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>Das bringen Sie pers&ouml;nlich mit:</b></h4>\n<ul><li>Analytisches Denken</li><li>\nSystematisch-methodisches Planen und Vorgehen</li><li>\nInitiative/ Eigenverantwortung</li><li>\nAdressaten- und Dienstleistungsorientierung</li><li>\nVerhandlungsf&auml;higkeit und -geschick</li></ul>\n<p>Mit Ihrer Bewerbung erkl&auml;ren Sie Ihre Bereitschaft zu gelegentlichen Dienstreisen und gelegentlicher Rufbereitschaft.</p>\n<p>Allerdings wird durch die Nutzung moderner Tools zur Zusammenarbeit und Kommunikation die Notwendigkeit von Dienstreisen auf ein Minimum reduziert.</p>\n</div></div><div><div><h2 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>ArbeitgeberLeistungen</b></h2>\n<p>Wir bieten Ihnen eine <b>unbefristete</b> Einstellung als Tarifbesch&auml;ftigte/-r. Das Entgelt entspricht bei Erf&uuml;llung der pers&ouml;nlichen Voraussetzungen der <b>Entgeltgruppe 12</b> des Tarifvertrags f&uuml;r den &ouml;ffentlichen Dienst (TV&ouml;D Bund). Die &Uuml;bernahme in ein Beamtenverh&auml;ltnis wird, soweit die Voraussetzungen hierf&uuml;r vorliegen, von Seiten des ITZBund angestrebt.</p>\n<p>F&uuml;r Beamtinnen und Beamte ist der Dienstposten nach <b>BesGr. A 12 BBesO</b> bewertet.</p>\n<p>Dar&uuml;ber hinaus zahlen wir eine <b>monatliche ITZBund-Zulage</b> in H&ouml;he von 160 &euro;.</p>\n<h4 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>\nDarauf k&ouml;nnen Sie sich freuen:</b></h4>\n<ul><li>Gesellschaftliche Verantwortung bei der Digitalisierung Deutschlands</li><li>\nAttraktive Gestaltung der IT des Bundes</li><li>\nArbeitsplatzsicherheit und die Vereinbarkeit von Familie, Pflege und Beruf durch moderne Arbeitszeitmodelle, wie z.B. Home-Office und gleitende Arbeitszeit</li><li>\nInteressante und qualifizierte Weiter- und Fortbildungen und vieles mehr</li><li>\nJobticket (bitte beachten: die M&ouml;glichkeit ein Jobticket abzuschlie&szlig;en besteht nicht an jedem Dienstsitz)</li></ul>\n</div></div><div><div><h2 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>Besondere Hinweise</b></h2>\n<p>Das ITZBund unterst&uuml;tzt die berufliche Gleichstellung von Frauen und M&auml;nnern und begr&uuml;&szlig;t deshalb besonders Bewerbungen von Frauen. Bewerbungen von schwerbehinderten und diesen gleichgestellten Menschen sind uns willkommen, von ihnen wird nur ein Mindestma&szlig; an k&ouml;rperlicher Eignung verlangt. Im Falle gleicher Eignung, Bef&auml;higung und fachlicher Leistung werden Frauen nach Ma&szlig;gabe des Bundesgleichstellungsgesetzes, schwerbehinderte Menschen und diesen gleichgestellte Menschen nach Ma&szlig;gabe des SGB IX bevorzugt ber&uuml;cksichtigt. Bewerbungen von Menschen mit Migrationshintergrund, die die Einstellungsvoraussetzungen erf&uuml;llen, sind ausdr&uuml;cklich erw&uuml;nscht. Die zu besetzende Stelle ist grunds&auml;tzlich f&uuml;r Teilzeitbesch&auml;ftigung geeignet, soweit keine zwingenden dienstlichen Belange entgegenstehen.</p>\n</div></div><div></div><div><div><h2 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>Ihre Bewerbung</b></h2>\n<h3 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>Haben wir Ihr Interesse geweckt?</b></h3>\n<p>Dann freuen wir uns auf Ihre aussagekr&auml;ftigen Bewerbungsunterlagen (Anschreiben, Lebenslauf, Pr&uuml;fungs- und Besch&auml;ftigungszeugnisse, ggf. Nachweis der Schwerbehinderung).</p>\n<p>Bitte senden Sie uns Ihre Bewerbung <b>bis zum 26.07.2021</b> &uuml;ber unser Online-Bewerbungssystem. Sie gelangen automatisch zum Bewerbungsportal, wenn Sie auf den Button &bdquo;Jetzt bewerben&ldquo; klicken.</p>\n<p>Das digitale Auswahlgespr&auml;ch findet <b>voraussichtlich in KW 34</b> statt.</p>\n<h3 class=\"jobSectionHeader\"><b>\nHaben Sie Fragen zu dieser Stellenausschreibung?</b></h3>\n<ul><li>Bei fachlichen Fragen zur Stellenausschreibung wenden Sie sich bitte an <b>Frau Dr. Wiebke Bedenknecht</b> (022899 680 8107) oder <b>Herr</b> <b>Wornowski</b> (0228/99680-8122).</li><li>\nBei personalwirtschaftlichen Fragen rund um das Arbeitsverh&auml;ltnis wenden Sie sich bitte telefonisch an <b>Frau Nissen</b> (Tel. 0228/99680-5392) oder <b>Frau Wittig</b> (Tel. 0228/99680-8007).</li></ul></div></div></div><p></p>"}
{"company_name": "trommsdorff + dr\u00fcner", "job_title": "DATA SCIENTIST", "job_description": "<div><p>TD Reply is an innovation and marketing consultancy and is part of the Reply Group. We take data-driven and execution-oriented approaches to drive organizational changes through meaningful insights. In our Berlin, Munich, and Beijing offices, we are around 90 thinkers, developers, analysts, designers, consultants, visualizers, futurologists, and organizers. We are working with international premium brands such as Adidas, BMW, and Coca-Cola to optimize their marketing and sales strategies. For our team in Berlin, we are looking for supports across multiple projects.</p>\n<p><b>\nThat&rsquo;s you</b></p>\n<p>\nWe drive innovation in marketing and data science and believe that magic happens when data science meets imagination. Great brands, however, will to also create great business value by supporting a company&rsquo;s actions. Together with our consultants, developers, and designers we help to build those products and drive the digital transformation of our clients. Therefore, we create data science solutions to predict the future of consumer behavior, to find the best media budget allocation, to guide brand management operations and to provide insights and management solutions on how to drive business. If you are also keen to shape the future of data driven management solutions and break down boundaries in marketing and data science, you are welcome in our data science team.</p>\n<p><b>\nYour tasks will include</b></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Crunching and describing data sets and important consumer/customer insights on structured and unstructured data</li>\n<li>Working on algorithms for a variety of business problems (e.g. sales predictions, media mix allocation, effect modelling) by applying your knowledge in statistics and machine learning</li>\n<li>Enabling our clients to extract insights from multiple data streams that build bridges between companies and customers</li>\n<li>Creating reports and interactive dashboards based on digital data sources (including web analytics, buzz tracking, CRM, online search behavior) and have the key data at your fingertips</li>\n<li>Presenting your findings in front of our team of consultants as well as our clients in a clearly understandable manner</li>\n</ul>\n<p><b>There is a match if&hellip;</b></p>\n<ul>\n<li>you hold a master&rsquo;s degree or above in the quantitative fields (e.g., Data Science, Computer Science, Statistics, or Economics) with at least 2+ years&rsquo; working experience</li>\n<li>you possess a deep understanding of statistical modelling, practical machine learning, and/or big data analytics</li>\n<li>your profile is completed by demonstrated skills in a relevant programming language such as Python and/or R</li>\n<li>you are familiar with basic cloud services such as Amazon Web Service, Google Cloud Platform, or Microsoft Azure</li>\n<li>you are experienced in working on business related research problems to provide insights with high business impacts</li>\n<li>you have a good knowledge of effectively writing, presenting, and communicating analytic results to other teams</li>\n</ul>\n<p><b>What&rsquo;s in it for you?</b></p>\n<p>\nYou will collaborate with an experienced and enthusiastic team of experts with a lot of ideas, great clients and challenging projects. We also have an awesome work environment, filled with great people with every imaginable kind of digital expertise. We will tailor a package that&rsquo;s just right for you.<br>\nApplicationWe want to hire you!</p>\n<p>\nOK, to be totally honest, we should qualify that statement: If you&rsquo;re talented, hard working, smart, brave, innovative, humble, confident, nice and love working in a data driven industry, then we want to hire you.</p>\n<p><b>\nInterested?</b></p>\n<p>\nPlease submit your resume to our REPLY Recruiter here.</p></div><p></p>"}
{"company_name": "South Pole Group", "job_title": "Climate Impact Data Scientist", "job_description": "<div><p>South Pole is an energetic, global company offering comprehensive sustainability solutions and services. With offices spanning all continents across the globe, we strive to create a sustainable society and economy that positively impacts our climate, ecosystems and developing communities. With our solutions we inspire and enable our customers to create value from sustainability-related activities.</p><p>\nOur Digital &amp; Data Science team helps our clients and South Pole design and execute the most ambitious and scalable climate impact initiatives whilst reducing the administrative effort to zero. Our unique track record of running projects across the globe and delivering verified, high quality carbon credits provides us with valuable data we can leverage to identify new, high impact initiatives. We help companies on a day-to-day basis to drive their carbon neutral strategies with their customers, suppliers and their employees through analytics and sustainability software solutions. If you have the skills, ambition and drive to use the best of digital and AI to protect ecosystems, restore forests, drive sustainable agriculture, and enable climate zero journeys across the globe then please apply or register your interest now!</p><p></p><p><b>\nJob summary:</b></p><p>\nIf you are looking to combine actionable insights, with real impact, this role is for you. As a Climate Impact Data Scientist, you will help tackle key questions that our clients have about the opportunities and risks that climate impacts have on their business models. In support of this quest, you will execute different types of analytics, build dashboards and help develop recommenders for best actions. In the process you will interact with and find ways to handle data from different sources such as raw climate model data, vulnerability data, facility information, GIS data and more. This will give you first hand experience in delivering insights to enable the most promising business models at the forefront of climate mitigation. And you will be part of the rapidly growing tribe of digital innovators at South Pole.</p><p></p><p><b>\nMain tasks &amp; responsibilities:</b></p><ul>\n<li>\nImplementation of complex data projects: Write scripts in python to access, enrich, clean, process and present data to address climate risk challenges\n</li><li>Supervision and implementation of projects facilitating the google cloud computing environment</li>\n<li>Development of automated workflows and building dashboards using python, sql and tableau</li>\n<li>Design, development and maintenance of database applications (sql)</li>\n<li>Collaborate closely with consultants and business developers to understand the goals and issues of the respective departments. Challenge their proposed solutions, and come up with creative alternative solutions that best support the business</li>\n<li>Explore and suggest new tools and methods to achieve maximal efficiency in data management</li>\n</ul><p></p><p><b>\nRequirements:</b></p><ul>\n<li>\nEducation in Engineering, Economics, Natural Sciences, IT, or any other relevant field that enabled the candidate to develop the core knowledge and skills</li>\n<li>2-4 years of work experience in this field of expertise\n</li><li>The following skills are a plus: Postgres, machine learning algorithms and tools, Natural Language Processing, google app maker, SOAP and/or data scraping</li>\n<li>Eagerness to understand and dive into the climate science and climate risk topic and define and address the data science aspect for our clients\n</li><li>Excellent planning and time management skills</li>\n<li>Oral and written command of English, other languages are advantages</li>\n<li>Self-driven and able to propose new ideas and take initiatives</li>\n<li>Comfortable working in an international fast-paced environment</li>\n</ul><p></p><p><b>\nWhat we offer:</b></p><p>\nAt South Pole, we care about our employees as much as we care about the planet. South Pole is not just an employer, we are a Team. South Pole does not just offer people a job, we offer you a career. By joining our team, you will find strong purpose and deep meaning in everything you do. You will have the chance to make a real difference for our clients and for the planet, working alongside a passionate team of like-minded colleagues, while building your knowledge/skills and developing your career in a fun, dynamic, international and fast-growing organisation.</p><p>\nWe&rsquo;re a planet of 7.5 billion unique and different people. We all have a contribution to make; South Pole is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, colour, sex, gender identity, sexual orientation, age, national origin, marital status or disability. Our recruitment is decided on the basis of qualifications, merit and business need.</p></div>"}
{"company_name": "Hypatos GmbH", "job_title": "Data Scientist (f/m/d)", "job_description": "<div>Your Mission\n<ul><li>As a member of our team you will have a significant impact on the technical direction of the company.</li><li>\nYou will be on the cutting edge of data science, and collaborate closely with other data scientists, machine learning engineers and key stakeholders to leverage established and novel data sources and machine learning techniques to deliver tools that integrate directly with our existing application landscape.</li><li>\nYou will work with state-of-the art machine learning and statistical models as a full-time data scientist, and deploy NLP/text mining models to production</li><li>\nYou will leverage recent advances in natural language understanding and AI to increase automation</li><li>\nYou will present machine learning approaches to stakeholders and clients from a non-technical discipline</li></ul>\nYour Profile\n<ul><li>Ph.D., M.Sc. or equivalent experience in Computer Science, Engineering, Statistics, or another relevant technical field</li><li>\nDeep technical knowledge in a variety of statistical and machine learning methods, such as: modern neural networks, tree-based models, regularized GLMs, and more</li><li>\nExperience with Python/R/Matlaband ML toolkits such as Torch, TensorFlow, Keras, Scikit-learn, CRAN, etc.</li><li>\nStrong skills in SQL and No-SQL databases</li><li>\nFamiliarity with IaaS solutions, such as Microsoft Azure, AWS, and Google Compute Engine is a plus</li><li>\nExperience with transitioning applications from R&amp;D into production is a big plus</li><li>\nMotivated self-starter with a strong enthusiasm to learn</li><li>\nStrong communication skills. You communicate complex data solutions across teams and clients</li></ul>\nOur Offer\n<ul><li>You will be able to personally and professionally grow with a young and striving company through technically challenging, diverse and increasingly international projects</li><li>\nBeyond an individually negotiated compensation package including company shares, you will enjoy a unique combination of professional opportunities, entrepreneurial spirit, technological excellence and industry exposure</li><li>\nFlat hierarchies and a large amount of individual responsibility</li><li>\nFlexible working hours and a pleasant working environment</li><li>\nPartial home office solution is possible</li></ul></div>"}
{"company_name": "Photon and Neutron Data ", "job_title": "Data Scientist", "job_description": "<div><p>As Data Scientist you will collect and prepare data and design of end-to-end analytical solutions and work side by side with the founders on growing the company.</p><p></p>\n<p><b>Tasks</b></p>\n<ul><li>Algorithm development and data visualisation</li><li>\nBe responsible for the continuous optimization of data input and model output</li><li>\nApply Data Mining, Predictive Analytics, Machine Learning and Big Data Technologies</li><li>\nCommunicate with clients to understand their situation and needs</li></ul><p><b><br>\nYour Profile</b></p>\n<ul><li>Good knowledge in Python (or R) and SQL</li><li>\nKnowledge of analytics and data science domains, including statistics and data analysis</li><li>\nIndependent working mentality, proactive attitude and an entrepreneurial mindset</li><li>\nAnalytical skills and an affinity for digital business</li><li>\nSolid communication skills in English</li></ul></div><p></p>"}
{"company_name": "VDI/VDE Innovation + Technik", "job_title": "Werkstudent Data Engineering (d/m/w)", "job_description": "<p><b>Ihre Aufgaben bei uns: </b></p><ul><li>Unterst\u00fctzung bei der Identifikation neuer Datenquellen und bei deren Integration in das Data-Warehouse</li><li>Aktualisierung von Forschungs- und Innovationsdaten im Data-Warehouse</li><li>Mitarbeit an der Zusammenf\u00fchrung, Deduplizierung und Qualit\u00e4tssicherung von Datens\u00e4tzen</li><li>Durchf\u00fchrung von Daten-Analysen auf Basis von Natural Language Processing</li><li>Mitwirkung an der Trainingsphase von neuronalen Netzen sowie an weiteren Projekten</li><li>Recherche zu und Evaluation von aktuellen Themen im Data-Science-Umfeld</li><li>\u00dcbernahme von organisatorischen und administrativen Office-T\u00e4tigkeiten</li></ul><p><b>Unsere Erwartungen an Sie: </b></p><ul><li>Laufendes Vollzeitstudium vorzugsweise der Informatik oder einer informatiknahen Studienrichtung (mit einer verbleibenden Studiendauer von mindestens 18 Monaten)</li><li>Interesse am Thema K\u00fcnstliche Intelligenz, idealerweise erg\u00e4nzt um erste praktische Erfahrungen bspw. im Rahmen eines Praktikums</li><li>Programmierkenntnisse im Bereich SQL und Python w\u00fcnschenswert</li><li>Systematische und selbstst\u00e4ndige Arbeitsweise mit einer hohen Dienstleistungsorientierung und Einsatzbereitschaft</li><li>Sehr gutes m\u00fcndliches und schriftliches Ausdrucksverm\u00f6gen in deutscher Sprache</li><li>Sicherer Umgang mit den g\u00e4ngigen MS Office-Anwendungen, insbesondere Excel</li></ul><p>Mehr zum Fachbereich erfahren Sie hier.</p><p>VDI/VDE-IT in drei Minuten</p><p>Die VDI/VDE Innovation + Technik GmbH ist ein f\u00fchrender Dienstleister, wenn es um Fragen zu Innovation und Technik geht. Unsere Mitarbeiter: innen arbeiten in interdisziplin\u00e4ren Teams als Expert: innen aus Natur-, Ingenieur-, Gesellschafts- und Wirtschaftswissenschaften zusammen. Wir unterst\u00fctzen und beraten bei der Analyse komplexer Vorhaben oder Marktsituationen, bei der F\u00f6rderung mit Forschungsprogrammen aus Bund, L\u00e4ndern und EU und organisieren Gesch\u00e4ftsstellen oder Kontaktb\u00fcros f\u00fcr Forschung und Wirtschaft.</p><p>Art der Stelle: Praktikum</p>"}
