{"company_name": "Stroer Media Ag", "job_title": "Data Science Working Student (human)", "job_description": "Zur Verst\u00e4rkung unseres Teams im Gesch\u00e4ftsbereich Str\u00f6er SSP GmbH suchen wir Dich als\u2026\n<br>Data Science Working Student (human)\n<br><br>\n<b>Art der Anstellung:</b> Werkstudent\n<br><br>\n<b>Standort:</b> Berlin\n<br><br>\n<b>Berufserfahrung:</b> Student/Praktikant\n<br><br>\n<b>Firma:</b> Str\u00f6er SSP GmbH\n<br><br>\n<b>Bereich:</b> IT\n<br><br>\nYou will...\n<br><br>\nbe a part of our experienced and inspired data science team.\n<br><br>\nwork with actual big data as our platform handles hundreds of thousands of requests per second and generates new data for each request.\n<br><br>\ndrive your models from design through implementation into operations.\n<br><br>\ntake responsibility for the stability and scalability of our data science stack.\n<br><br>\ninteract with our international technology partners in Czechia and New Zealand.\n<br><br>\nYou have...\n<br><br>\nA knack for analyzing data, you are tech-enthusiastic and you are a fast learner .\n<br><br>\nknowledge of theoretical and applied statistics and machine learning .\n<br><br>\nexperience in a programming language, ideally Python , and relevant Data Science modules as well as interest in Spark .\n<br><br>\nideally first experiences working with databases .\n<br><br>\nideally experience with development tooling such as the terminal and git .\n<br><br>\ninterest in working in a dynamic and mixed-technology service landscape, using technologies such as Java , Scala and JavaScript , among others.\n<br><br>\ninterest in in building highly scalable and distributed machine learning systems in the cloud and/or on premise .\n<br><br>\na desire to quickly learn new technologies and work on existing code.\n<br><br>\nWe offer...\n<br><br>\na small and highly passionate team of extraordinary co-workers.\n<br><br>\nan open, embracing and inclusive culture.\n<br><br>\nan agile, focused, yet relaxed atmosphere with flexible working hours (usually about 20 hours per week).\n<br><br>\na high level of freedom and responsibility.\n<br><br>\na competitive salary.\n<br><br>\na nice and spacious office right at Rosa-Luxemburg-Platz.\n<br><br>\n<b>many goodies:</b> a well stocked kitchen, German classes and regular team events with catered lunch if there is no ongoing pandemic.\n<br><br>\nPlease note that we cannot offer fully remote positions outside of Berlin and that you must be enrolled at a university.\n<br><br>\nStr\u00f6er Labs\u2019 core business is highly efficient real-time advertising. We are 100% science- and technology-focused and process and analyze massive amounts of data. We are working at the cutting edge of big data, machine learning and real-time technologies and we are operating large-scale deployments of real-time web services.\n<br><br>\n<b>We are looking for a:</b><br>\nData Science Working Student (human)\n<br><br>\nApply now!"}
